============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is a programming language?
A1: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

Q2: What is artificial intelligence?
A2: AI is the simulation of human intelligence by machines,
     including learning, reasoning, and problem-solving.
     Types: narrow AI (specific tasks) and general AI
     (human-level across domains).

Q3: What is the water cycle?
A3: Water evaporates from oceans/lakes, rises and condenses
     into clouds, falls as precipitation, and flows back via
     rivers and groundwater. Driven by solar energy.

Q4: What is the Big Bang?
A4: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

Q5: What is democracy?
A5: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

